q(
"""<b>1.</b> You and your partner are working a foot post near the Capitol complex when you see a man (Ray) arguing with a woman (Lena) over a phone. Ray suddenly shoves Lena hard with both hands, and she falls into a metal stanchion, cutting her cheek. Lena stands up, dizzy, and Ray says, “I’m not done,” then grabs a broken stanchion pole and raises it over his shoulder as if to swing. You draw your taser and command Ray to drop it. Ray backs up, keeps the pole raised, and takes two steps toward Lena before dropping it and trying to walk away. Medical later documents stitches and a mild concussion. What is the <u>best</u> charge for Ray?""",
[
    "Simple Assault",
    "Aggravated Assault",
    "Assault with a Dangerous Weapon (ADW)",
    "Threats to do Bodily Harm"
],
2,
"Multiple charges could be considered (assault and threats), but the raised metal pole used in a menacing manner elevates the assault to ADW. The injury occurred during the assault, but the key enhancement here is the dangerous weapon used to threaten/assault.",
"Legal"
)

q(
