"Avenues cut diagonally and are typically named for states (with noted exceptions), and they generally do not dictate block numbers.",
"Non-Legal"
)

q(
"""<b>45.</b> Prior notification for armed LEO/agent admittance into Capitol Buildings is typically distributed by:""",
[
    "The Library of Congress",
    "Special Events Section or Watch Commander",
    "The U.S. Marshals Service only",
    "The complainant officer"
],
1,
"Prior notification is issued/distributed by Special Events Section (or Watch Commander after hours) via VIP/FYI-type notifications to division offices.",
"Non-Legal"
)

q(
"""<b>46.</b> For an on-duty LEO/agent entering a Capitol Building armed on official business with proper escort and credentials, the correct screening rule is:""",
[
    "Administrative search is always required",
    "No administrative search is required",
    "They must surrender the firearm to CSS",
    "They may enter unescorted with no verification"
],
1,
"With verified credentials, escort, and authorized firearm on official business, no administrative search is required (per your notes).",
"Non-Legal"
)

q(
"""<b>47.</b> A LEO arrives armed <u>without</u> prior notification and is <u>alone</u> (visiting/sightseeing). Best procedure is:""",
[
    "Deny entry permanently",
    "Verify credentials through SES, arrange escort to secure weapon in a lock box, conduct administrative search",
    "Allow entry with firearm if they claim to be a police officer",
    "Have them leave the grounds immediately while still armed"
],
1,
"Without prior notification and not on official business, weapons must be secured (lock box), credentials verified through SES, and an administrative search conducted prior to entry.",
"Non-Legal"
)

q(
"""<b>48.</b> Members of Congress may carry a firearm into Capitol Buildings provided it is:""",
[
    "Loaded and concealed",
    "Unloaded and securely wrapped",
    "Registered in any state",
    "Carried only by staff"
],
1,
"Per your notes: Member may carry if unloaded and securely wrapped; notify a supervisor and escort to destination.",
"Non-Legal"
)

q(
"""<b>49.</b> Complaints against USCP employees may be made:""",
[
    "Only in writing",
    "Only in person",
    "In person, by phone, or in writing (including anonymous complaints)",
    "Only through the Inspector General"
],
2,
"Policy notes: complaints may be made in person, over the telephone, or in writing; anonymous complaints are accepted for investigation.",
"Non-Legal"
)

q(
"""<b>50.</b> The form used when completing a complaint report (when a supervisor is not available) is:""",
[
    "CP-76",
    "CP-536",
    "CP-534",
    "CP-550"
],
1,
"CP-536 is the complaint report form per the complaint and disciplinary process notes.",
"Non-Legal"
)

q(
"""<b>51.</b> Category I complaints include which of the following?" "",
[
    "Courtesy violations",
    "Truthfulness/Integrity violations",
    "Minor policy violations",
    "Carrying of credentials issues"
],
1,
"Category I includes serious allegations such as excessive force, false arrest, discrimination/civil rights violations, criminal statute violations, and truthfulness/integrity issues.",
"Non-Legal"
)

q(
"""<b>52.</b> Sworn Category I administrative investigations have a timeframe of:""",
[
    "60 days",
    "95 days",
    "120 days",
