"Non-Legal"
)

q(
"""<b>53.</b> Weingarten Rights generally apply to:""",
[
    "All supervisors only",
    "Bargaining unit employees who are entitled to union representation during interviews that could lead to discipline",
    "Only criminal interviews after Miranda",
    "Only OIG investigations"
],
1,
"Weingarten Rights support bargaining-unit employees requesting union representation in interviews that could lead to discipline or affect working conditions.",
"Non-Legal"
)

q(
"""<b>54.</b> Garrity Rights are best summarized as:""",
[
    "You may remain silent in any workplace interview",
    "You are compelled to answer in an administrative investigation, and those statements are protected from criminal use (as applicable)",
    "You must be read Miranda before any questioning",
    "Only applies to civilians"
],
1,
"Garrity: compelled administrative statements; Miranda is separate and relates to criminal custodial interrogation.",
"Non-Legal"
)

q(
"""<b>55.</b> In the USCP organizational structure, a <i>Bureau</i> is best defined as:""",
[
    "A small team with collateral duties",
    "The largest organizational element, commanded by a Bureau Commander/Office Director reporting to the COP/CAO",
    "A unit commanded by a Sergeant",
